HEADWORD: Testicardines
<hw>Tes`ti*car"di*nes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Test</er> a shell, and <er>Cardo</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of brachiopods including those which have a calcareous
shell furnished with a hinge and hinge teeth. Terebratula and Spirifer
are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

